    {
      "num": 11,
      "text": "A CFE is retained as an expert witness in a civil fraud case. The opposing counsel seeks to exclude the expert's testimony regarding financial statement analysis methodology. Under Federal Rule of Evidence 702 and Daubert standard, which factor is MOST CRITICAL for admissibility?",
      "tag": "Expert Witness Testimony - Daubert Standard",
      "options": [
        "A. Whether the expert possesses a relevant professional certification (CPA, CFE, CFA) demonstrating baseline competence",
        "B. Whether the methodology is sufficiently reliable, grounded in established scientific or technical principles, and testable—not speculative conjecture",
