      "correct": 1,
      "justification_correct": "Daubert (509 U.S. 579, 1993) requires methodology reliability: testability, peer review, error rates, general acceptance. FRE 702 mandates reliable methods/principles. Certification supports qualifications but insufficient alone; alignment with counsel contradicts independence. Reliability is gatekeeping criterion.",
      "justification_wrong": "Certification aids qualification but doesn't ensure methodology reliability. Prior courtroom success is credential irrelevant to Daubert. Alignment with counsel's theory violates expert independence and FRE 702(a) requirement that opinion assist fact-finder, not advocate.",
