        "Give a brief overview but withhold specific details until you receive additional compensation for disclosing proprietary methods"
      ],
      "correct_answer": 1,
      "explanation": "As an expert witness, you have a duty to be transparent about your methodology during deposition. Option B is correct because expert witnesses are expected to fully disclose their methods, procedures, and bases for their opinions during discovery, including depositions. This allows opposing counsel to properly evaluate and potentially challenge your expert opinion. Option A is incorrect because expert witnesses generally cannot claim trade secret protection for their methodologies in litigation. Option C is incorrect because depositions are part of the discovery process where experts must answer questions about their methodology. Option D is incorrect because it suggests unethical behavior; experts should not condition their testimony on additional payment beyond their agreed-upon fees.",
      "tags": [
        "expert witness",
